cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CYBER, cs.CR 

The paper focuses on the evaluation of an explanation method for machine learning predictions in the context of alert processing, which involves human decision-making. This suggests a strong connection to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with machine learning interpretability (cs.AI) and model-agnostic explanations (cs.LG). The context of alert processing also suggests a connection to cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and potentially to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR).
